...until they've stolen enough
to go into exile somewhere else.

243
00:25:45,892 --> 00:25:48,518
And the rebels, they're not sure
they want to take over.

244
00:25:48,694 --> 00:25:51,025
Otherwise,
they'd have to govern this mess.

245
00:25:51,196 --> 00:25:53,494
- But TIA, right, M'Ed?
- TIA.

246
00:25:53,665 --> 00:25:54,894
What's TIA?

247
00:25:55,534 --> 00:25:59,435
- "This is Africa," huh?
- Right.

248
00:26:00,004 --> 00:26:02,471
- You want another?
- Sure.

249
00:26:06,276 --> 00:26:08,800
So which one are you?

250
00:26:10,281 --> 00:26:13,545
- Smuggler?
- Am I?

251
00:26:13,716 --> 00:26:16,651
Somehow you don't strike me
as the UNICEF type.

252
00:26:17,687 --> 00:26:19,655
How about soldier of fortune?

253
00:26:20,123 --> 00:26:22,682
Or is that too much of a cliché?

254
00:26:22,858 --> 00:26:24,189
Diamonds?

255
00:26:24,893 --> 00:26:28,488
- If I told you I was a missionary...?
- For Van De Kaap?

256
00:26:30,198 --> 00:26:32,792
Better watch that type of talk,
Miss Bowen.

257
00:26:32,967 --> 00:26:36,061
In America, it's bling-bling,
but out here, it's bling-bang, huh?

258
00:26:36,337 --> 00:26:39,465
I wouldn't want you
getting in any trouble.

259
00:26:40,739 --> 00:26:43,005
How much trouble
do you think I would get into...

260
00:26:43,177 --> 00:26:46,441
...for talking about blood diamonds?

261
00:26:49,248 --> 00:26:52,309
- You're a journalist.
- That's right.

262
00:26:56,255 --> 00:26:57,845
Piss off, huh?

263
00:27:02,192 --> 00:27:05,457
For five years, this country has reported
almost no diamond exports...

264
00:27:05,629 --> 00:27:09,290
...while Liberia, right next door,
has exported 2 billion dollars' worth.

265
00:27:09,464 --> 00:27:12,490
Very odd, considering that Liberia
has no diamonds to speak of.

266
00:27:12,667 --> 00:27:13,657
I'm shocked.

267
00:27:13,836 --> 00:27:17,167
Van De Kaap denies trading blood
diamonds, but admits it's impossible...

268
00:27:17,338 --> 00:27:21,671
...to tell where a diamond comes from
unless their smuggler gets caught.

269
00:27:21,842 --> 00:27:23,538
What do you want from me, huh?

270
00:27:23,710 --> 00:27:28,237
You know all about Van De Kaap.
Help me out. Off the record.

271
00:27:28,481 --> 00:27:32,942
Well, off the record, I like to get kissed
before I get fucked, huh?

272
00:27:35,521 --> 00:27:36,715
Shit.

273
00:28:10,052 --> 00:28:13,544
- Cordell. How is it, Shona?
- Long time, pal.

274
00:28:13,722 --> 00:28:17,087
- How's Alice?
- She's well, thanks.

275
00:28:17,257 --> 00:28:19,088
Tim must be in school, right?

276
00:28:19,259 --> 00:28:21,591
- Big kids, big problems, you know?
- Yeah, yeah.

277
00:28:21,761 --> 00:28:24,354
I heard you got into a spot of trouble
in the bush, huh?

278
00:28:24,531 --> 00:28:26,929
<i>Well, you know the bush, right, bru?</i>

279
00:28:27,699 --> 00:28:30,260
- Company doing well?
- Can't complain.

280
00:28:30,436 --> 00:28:33,064
Eleven wars in the continent.
We're keeping busy.

281
00:28:33,239 --> 00:28:35,672
So, what, you're here on holiday, huh?

282
00:28:37,375 --> 00:28:39,275
- How's the colonel?
- He sends his regards.

283
00:28:39,444 --> 00:28:43,140
Good, good. Score us a loose, huh?

284
00:28:44,248 --> 00:28:46,442
<i>Smoking will kill you, bru.</i>

285
00:28:46,716 --> 00:28:47,945
Only if I live, right?

286
00:28:53,289 --> 00:28:55,188
<i>That's for breaking my TV, bru.</i>

287
00:29:00,062 --> 00:29:03,588
Tell the colonel he'll get his money.
I'll come see him soon.

288
00:29:10,338 --> 00:29:11,566
Ten more.

289
00:29:11,739 --> 00:29:14,640
Come. Come.

290
00:29:20,748 --> 00:29:22,238
Go on.

291
00:29:36,426 --> 00:29:40,362
Dia. Dia. Come here.
Get away from there.

292
00:29:40,964 --> 00:29:43,625
Go. Go, Mama.

293
00:29:43,799 --> 00:29:45,733
Stay down.

294
00:30:03,850 --> 00:30:05,511
Excuse me,
my name's Solomon Vandy--

295
00:30:05,685 --> 00:30:07,779
- Check the list.
- I have checked the list.

296
00:30:07,953 --> 00:30:12,413
- File papers at the Office for Refugees.
- Sir, I have filed papers with the office.

297
00:30:12,591 --> 00:30:14,581
Then God help you,
because I can't.

298
00:30:14,760 --> 00:30:15,818
- Please, sir--
- Next.

299
00:30:15,995 --> 00:30:18,122
- Sir-- Sir, no, please.
- Hey, hey. Me, me, me.

300
00:30:18,297 --> 00:30:22,062
Husband here. One year we look.

301
00:30:26,572 --> 00:30:28,733
Hurry, Mom. Go.

302
00:30:33,911 --> 00:30:35,277
Dia! Dia!

303
00:30:35,446 --> 00:30:36,436
- Jassie!
- Dia!

304
00:30:36,613 --> 00:30:38,204
- Mama!
- Dia!

305
00:30:38,381 --> 00:30:40,543
Jassie! Mama!

306
00:31:02,802 --> 00:31:05,633
He's been waiting.
What took you?

307
00:31:06,337 --> 00:31:09,704
What are you gonna do,
shoot me right here, huh, Shona?

308
00:31:09,874 --> 00:31:12,969
Now, don't be a wanker, man. Get in.

309
00:31:45,039 --> 00:31:47,439
- Hello, Danny.
- Colonel.

310
00:31:47,609 --> 00:31:49,405
You look well.

311
00:31:49,576 --> 00:31:52,738
Clean living and a pure heart,
I suppose, huh?

312
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:54,775
Walk with me.

313
00:31:56,550 --> 00:31:59,383
It seems the rebels have taken back
the diamond fields, Danny.

314
00:31:59,553 --> 00:32:01,884
The government
of Sierra Leone has contracted us...

315
00:32:02,054 --> 00:32:04,023
...to go in there
and take the rebels down.

316
00:32:04,191 --> 00:32:05,783
So you sell the rebels weapons...

317
00:32:05,958 --> 00:32:08,619
...the government hires you
when they use them? Nice, sir.

318
00:32:09,095 --> 00:32:11,961
I assume you're asking
for mining concessions, huh?

319
00:32:12,130 --> 00:32:15,256
We save the government,
they show their gratitude.

320
00:32:15,432 --> 00:32:17,730
And you get rich, right?

321
00:32:22,038 --> 00:32:23,596
How long have I known you, Danny?

322
00:32:24,039 --> 00:32:27,201
I was... I was 19, sir.

323
00:32:27,443 --> 00:32:31,971
And you survived.
A lot of boys didn't. Why is that?

324
00:32:33,381 --> 00:32:36,043
Just lucky, I guess.

325
00:32:37,952 --> 00:32:42,820
No, you were a good soldier.
But I made you better, didn't I?

326
00:32:46,193 --> 00:32:47,627
Yes, sir. Yes, you did.

327
00:32:47,794 --> 00:32:50,820
And over the years,
didn't I protect you...

328
00:32:51,230 --> 00:32:55,189
...teach you about diamonds,
cut you in on the deals?

329
00:32:55,368 --> 00:32:59,029
- Some might call it that, yeah.
- But not you...

330
00:33:00,004 --> 00:33:03,667
...because you done with me now, eh?
On to bigger things.

331
00:33:06,811 --> 00:33:09,278
I need a man that knows
his way around up there.

332
00:33:09,447 --> 00:33:13,212
Unless, of course,
you wanna cut me in. Something pink?

333
00:33:14,284 --> 00:33:15,808
Sir...

334
00:33:15,986 --> 00:33:18,112
Our deal went bad,
and you owe me money.

335
00:33:18,287 --> 00:33:20,017
I'll take a stone as payment.

336
00:33:20,190 --> 00:33:24,058
Look, do you think if I found a stone
like that, I'd still be on this continent?

337
00:33:24,227 --> 00:33:28,061
- Come on.
- Danny, give me your hand.

338
00:33:31,066 --> 00:33:34,795
That's red earth. It's in our skin.

339
00:33:35,267 --> 00:33:37,668
The Shona say the color
comes from all the blood...

340
00:33:37,837 --> 00:33:40,397
...that's being spilled
fighting over the land.

341
00:33:42,442 --> 00:33:47,003
This is home.
You'll never leave Africa.

342
00:33:49,780 --> 00:33:52,443
If you say so, sir.

343
00:34:07,964 --> 00:34:11,592
So, what did you do, bury it?

344
00:34:12,800 --> 00:34:16,362
Yeah. Yeah, I would have
buried it, huh?

345
00:34:16,539 --> 00:34:20,565
<i>- What are you talking about?
- What am I talking about? Come on, bru.</i>

346
00:34:20,742 --> 00:34:22,176
I'm late for work.

347
00:34:22,344 --> 00:34:24,868
Pink, huh? The biggest one
he'd ever seen.

348
00:34:25,047 --> 00:34:27,173
<i>You were in the mining camps,
weren't you, bru?</i>

349
00:34:27,348 --> 00:34:30,839
Why else would that rebel with
the bandaged arm make up such a story?

350
00:34:31,018 --> 00:34:33,248
Go ask him.

351
00:34:47,567 --> 00:34:48,795
Thank you.

352
00:34:58,441 --> 00:35:01,238
Your mothers and fathers,
your brothers and sisters are dead.

353
00:35:01,411 --> 00:35:03,275
- You are dead! You have been reborn.
- No!

354
00:35:03,444 --> 00:35:06,675
- We are your family now.
- No! No!

355
00:35:14,555 --> 00:35:16,887
Your parents are weak.

356
00:35:17,458 --> 00:35:21,894
They're the farmers.
They're the fishermen.

357
00:35:22,394 --> 00:35:25,957
They've done nothing
but suck the blood from this country.

358
00:35:27,334 --> 00:35:31,793
But you are the heroes
who will save this nation.

359
00:35:32,070 --> 00:35:34,039
You are not children anymore.

360
00:35:35,041 --> 00:35:36,974
You're men.

361
00:35:39,177 --> 00:35:42,340
No one has ever given you respect...

362
00:35:42,514 --> 00:35:45,607
...but with this in your hand,
they go fear you.

363
00:35:45,783 --> 00:35:48,274
If you do not get
the respect you deserve...

364
00:35:48,453 --> 00:35:50,749
...you will take it
by shedding their blood.

365
00:35:50,921 --> 00:35:54,880
- Repeat after me, shed their blood.
- Shed their blood.

366
00:35:55,058 --> 00:35:58,118
- Louder! Shed their blood! Shed their blood!
- Shed their blood!

367
00:35:58,295 --> 00:36:01,423
Make them hear you in Freetown.
Shed their blood! Shed their blood!

368
00:36:01,598 --> 00:36:04,157
<i>Shed their blood! Shed their blood!
Shed their blood!</i>

369
00:36:04,333 --> 00:36:07,233
<i>- Dia Vandy, stand up.
- Shed their blood! Shed their blood!</i>

370
00:36:07,402 --> 00:36:10,303
<i>- Shed their blood! Shed their blood!
- Put your hand on the gun.</i>

371
00:36:10,472 --> 00:36:12,064
<i>Shed their blood!
Shed their blood!</i>

372
00:36:12,240 --> 00:36:13,830
<i>Shed their blood!
Shed their blood!</i>

373
00:36:14,006 --> 00:36:17,034
<i>- Shed their blood! Shed their blood!
- Now squeeze the trigger.</i>

374
00:36:17,577 --> 00:36:21,980
Come on, Dia. Pull the trigger.
Pull the trigger!

375
00:36:56,110 --> 00:37:00,671
I know, I know.
It's hard to be a man.

376
00:37:01,416 --> 00:37:03,942
Sit up. Come.

377
00:37:04,119 --> 00:37:08,418
But you are a soldier
of the revolution now.

378
00:37:08,623 --> 00:37:11,489
And I am your commander.

379
00:37:11,992 --> 00:37:13,857
Whatever you need...

380
00:37:14,027 --> 00:37:17,258
...guns, CDs, food...

381
00:37:17,431 --> 00:37:21,093
...come to me.
I will take care of you.

382
00:37:24,402 --> 00:37:30,808
Today, you are promoted
to the rank of captain.

383
00:37:35,410 --> 00:37:37,402
Dia Vandy...

384
00:37:39,014 --> 00:37:40,846
...boss man.

385
00:37:58,598 --> 00:38:00,225
<i>How's it, bru?</i>

386
00:38:00,766 --> 00:38:03,930
- You got something for me, huh?
- Yeah.

387
00:38:04,705 --> 00:38:08,104
- So, what's new, M'Ed?
- Fucking RUF.

388
00:38:08,274 --> 00:38:10,797
Tried to hit the government building
across the street.

389
00:38:10,976 --> 00:38:15,640
Shit, man, half the people
be soldiers today, RUF tomorrow.

390
00:38:15,814 --> 00:38:19,214
- Might be time to get your family out, huh?
- And go where?

391
00:38:19,383 --> 00:38:23,115
Just fire up the chopper
and fly away like you people?

392
00:38:23,489 --> 00:38:25,319
This my country, man.

393
00:38:25,490 --> 00:38:28,947
We here long before you came,
long after you gone.

394
00:38:37,968 --> 00:38:41,131
- Hi. I'm Maddy Bowen.
- How about you dance with me?

395
00:38:41,304 --> 00:38:44,670
- No, I don't dance.
- Neither do I. Come on.

396
00:38:49,878 --> 00:38:52,276
- So, Danny...
- Archer.

397
00:38:52,578 --> 00:38:53,636
Archer.

398
00:38:54,647 --> 00:38:58,207
When did you first start
moving stones? Was it Angola?

399
00:38:59,986 --> 00:39:04,581
Then you did the whole
mercenary thing. Was that fun?

400
00:39:06,123 --> 00:39:09,787
So, what are you?
Nihilist? Opportunist?

401
00:39:09,995 --> 00:39:12,121
Maybe I wasn't breast-fed
as a child, huh?

402
00:39:14,265 --> 00:39:16,699
You think I haven't met
people like you before?

403
00:39:16,866 --> 00:39:20,232
- I think you get off on people like me.
- You think?

404
00:39:22,972 --> 00:39:25,497
When did you first start
working for Van De Kaap?

405
00:39:26,075 --> 00:39:27,702
Christ, you never stop, do you?

406
00:39:28,977 --> 00:39:32,344
No, I never stop.

407
00:39:33,048 --> 00:39:34,639
Do you want me to stop?

408
00:39:36,018 --> 00:39:39,920
Why don't we go back to your place,
see what's in the minibar, huh?

409
00:39:40,087 --> 00:39:42,181
I'm a print journalist. I drank it.

410
00:39:43,457 --> 00:39:46,186
Is it possible that you don't care
how many people die...

411
00:39:46,360 --> 00:39:48,259
...because of the deals you do?

412
00:39:48,428 --> 00:39:51,659
People here kill each other as a way of life.
Always been like that.

413
00:39:51,933 --> 00:39:54,764
So you can just watch it
and go about your day?

414
00:39:56,069 --> 00:39:58,161
Maybe we should all just
write about it, then.

415
00:39:58,338 --> 00:40:00,670
Look, thanks for the dance, huh?

416
00:40:02,874 --> 00:40:06,242
- And a shot too, huh, M'Ed?
- Sure.

417
00:40:10,081 --> 00:40:11,378
You're a hard case, huh?

418
00:40:11,547 --> 00:40:14,539
Tell me something,
how long you been here in Africa, huh?

419
00:40:14,750 --> 00:40:18,049
Three months. And before that,
Afghanistan and Bosnia.

420
00:40:18,354 --> 00:40:20,446
You come here
with your laptop computer...

421
00:40:20,622 --> 00:40:24,558
...and your malaria medicine
and your little bottles of hand sanitizer.

422
00:40:25,326 --> 00:40:28,354
Think you're gonna change
the outcome, huh?

423
00:40:28,530 --> 00:40:31,123
Let me tell you something.
You sell blood diamonds too.

424
00:40:31,298 --> 00:40:32,788
- Really?
- Yeah.

425
00:40:32,967 --> 00:40:33,957
Tell me, how is that?

426
00:40:34,134 --> 00:40:36,397
Who do you think buys
the stones that I bring out?

427
00:40:36,569 --> 00:40:40,197
Dreamy American girls who all want
a storybook wedding and a big, shiny rock...

428
00:40:40,373 --> 00:40:43,934
...like the ones in the advertisements
of your politically-correct magazines.

429
00:40:44,110 --> 00:40:47,102
So, please, don't come here
and make judgments on me, all right?

430
00:40:48,513 --> 00:40:52,813
I provide a service. The world wants what
we have, and they want it cheap.

431
00:40:52,985 --> 00:40:56,214
We're in business together.
Get over yourself, darling.

432
00:40:56,687 --> 00:41:00,783
Okay, just to clarify, not all American girls
want a storybook wedding...

433
00:41:00,959 --> 00:41:03,859
...just like not all Africans kill each other
as a way of life.

434
00:41:04,028 --> 00:41:06,427
And yeah, it's a shit, shit world,
but you know what?

435
00:41:06,597 --> 00:41:10,464
Good things are done every day,
just, apparently, not by you.

436
00:41:12,068 --> 00:41:15,094
This place is about to explode.

437
00:41:15,372 --> 00:41:17,396
I wanna spend my time
with someone else.

438
00:41:28,483 --> 00:41:31,506
<i>You are listening to BBC World Service.</i>

439
00:41:31,683 --> 00:41:35,415
<i>In Sierra Leone, Revolutionary United Front
forces have been sighted...</i>

440
00:41:35,588 --> 00:41:38,318
<i>...within 10 kilometers
of the capital city of Freetown.</i>

441
00:41:38,491 --> 00:41:41,152
<i>The minister of the interior
has expressed confidence...</i>

442
00:41:41,325 --> 00:41:43,691
<i>...that the government troops
can repel the attack.</i>

443
00:41:43,862 --> 00:41:47,127
<i>All foreign nationals are being advised
to leave the country.</i>

444
00:41:47,299 --> 00:41:49,459
<i>There are also unconfirmed reports...</i>

445
00:41:49,633 --> 00:41:53,694
<i>...that atrocities are being committed by
both sides in the rapidly worsening situation.</i>

446
00:41:53,871 --> 00:41:57,805
<i>The United Nations has described
the refugee situation as critical.</i>

447
00:42:09,384 --> 00:42:11,784
Don't tell me you're gonna try
and sell it yourself.

448
00:42:11,955 --> 00:42:14,478
To who?
And for what price, my friend?

449
00:42:14,655 --> 00:42:16,680
You need my help,
whether you like it or not.

450
00:42:16,857 --> 00:42:19,917
- What are you talking about?
- Here, let me help you with that.

451
00:42:20,094 --> 00:42:23,961
You hear that? You hear that?
They came into the city overnight.

452
00:42:24,131 --> 00:42:26,429
It's started.
What are you gonna do now, huh?

453
00:42:26,599 --> 00:42:30,899
Listen, the right stone can buy anything.
Information, safety, even freedom.

454
00:42:31,071 --> 00:42:33,504
But a big stone does not stay secret
for very long.

455
00:42:33,672 --> 00:42:36,937
The moment you tell anyone about it,
your life is absolutely worthless.

456
00:42:37,110 --> 00:42:40,238
The only reason you're alive is
you haven't told anyone where it is.

457
00:42:40,413 --> 00:42:41,673
Am I right? Am I?

458
00:42:42,080 --> 00:42:44,105
Who do you think got you
out of jail, huh?

459
00:42:44,282 --> 00:42:47,342
- That makes us partners.
- I am not your partner!

460
00:42:47,518 --> 00:42:50,009
What if I helped you find your family?

461
00:42:50,186 --> 00:42:51,710
What do you know of my family?

462
00:42:51,886 --> 00:42:54,913
The relief agencies are useless,
the hospitals are overwhelmed.

463
00:42:55,091 --> 00:42:57,685
<i>- There are other ways, bru.
- Liar.</i>

464
00:42:57,860 --> 00:43:01,089
Look at me. I know people, huh?
White people.

465
00:43:01,261 --> 00:43:04,389
Without me, you're just another
black man in Africa, all right?

466
00:43:07,769 --> 00:43:09,496
Oh, shit.

467
00:43:11,238 --> 00:43:12,830
We got no time.
What's it gonna be?

468
00:43:13,007 --> 00:43:14,997
You would say anything.
How can I trust you?

469
00:43:15,174 --> 00:43:18,574
I don't give a fuck about you, all right?
That diamond could be priceless!

470
00:43:18,744 --> 00:43:23,011
We split it, and you get your family.
What's it gonna be, yes or no? Yes or no?

471
00:43:23,182 --> 00:43:25,776
- Where will we go? Where do we go?
- Come on, follow me!

