711
01:05:47,688 --> 01:05:50,020
...fifteen kilometers
from the Liberian border...

712
01:05:50,191 --> 01:05:52,820
- ...near the Moa River...
- As you can see behind me...

713
01:05:52,994 --> 01:05:54,518
...just a few minutes ago...

714
01:05:54,696 --> 01:05:57,027
- ...an ambulance has...
- Got movement in the bush.

715
01:05:57,231 --> 01:05:59,256
- Check out the head of the road.
- Spread out.

716
01:05:59,433 --> 01:06:01,162
--at this site.
Dozens of--

717
01:06:02,168 --> 01:06:04,102
Many are injured.

718
01:06:14,246 --> 01:06:17,409
Get back on the bus, huh?
Get back on! Come on!

719
01:06:17,583 --> 01:06:19,210
- Maddy!
- Move it! Move it!

720
01:06:19,385 --> 01:06:20,373
Get back on the bus!

721
01:06:20,552 --> 01:06:22,109
Solomon! Solomon!

722
01:06:22,286 --> 01:06:23,777
- Let's go.
- Solomon, come here!

723
01:06:23,957 --> 01:06:25,388
- Go, go, go.
- Come on, come on.

724
01:06:25,590 --> 01:06:28,253
- Get in the bus!
- Move, move, move! Come on, come on.

725
01:06:28,594 --> 01:06:30,423
- Move!
- Get in the bus. Let's go.

726
01:06:30,594 --> 01:06:32,790
Get in, get in.
Goddamn it, get in! Get in!

727
01:06:32,963 --> 01:06:35,397
- Let me inside!
- There's no fucking space!

728
01:06:35,565 --> 01:06:37,829
- Let them on the bus.
- You give him your seat.

729
01:06:38,002 --> 01:06:40,968
What if we just take your place, huh?
What if we take your place?

730
01:06:41,135 --> 01:06:44,069
That's enough. He can ride with me.
Oi, he can ride with me.

731
01:06:44,238 --> 01:06:46,799
Maddy! Let's go!
Maddy, let's go. Come on!

732
01:06:59,719 --> 01:07:02,846
Nothing like a little bang-bang
to get the heart started, Maddy.

733
01:07:03,722 --> 01:07:06,919
- Whatever you say, Corbauld.
- Come on, love. Don't be like that.

734
01:07:07,091 --> 01:07:10,549
Story's played out, hasn't it?
Government bad, rebels worse.

735
01:07:11,097 --> 01:07:13,531
No one gives a toss anymore.
Know what I mean?

736
01:07:49,297 --> 01:07:51,230
<i>This medicine will make you strong...</i>

737
01:07:51,766 --> 01:07:54,165
...make you invisible to your enemies.

738
01:07:54,334 --> 01:07:56,565
Bullets will bounce off you.

739
01:08:07,377 --> 01:08:11,142
Superboy Killer, yes, huh?
Commando.

740
01:08:12,315 --> 01:08:14,250
Foreigners are the cause of the problems.

741
01:08:16,852 --> 01:08:20,687
Poppy Sankoh say,
"Overthrow those who would exploit you."

742
01:08:22,558 --> 01:08:24,048
I am Baby Killer.

743
01:08:27,828 --> 01:08:31,492
- I am the Master of Disaster.
- You will be strong.

744
01:08:34,836 --> 01:08:36,267
I am Born Trouble.

745
01:08:42,675 --> 01:08:44,734
I am See Me No More.

746
01:08:54,286 --> 01:08:57,221
You'd think they'd want
at least one decent road in this place.

747
01:08:58,657 --> 01:09:02,787
I'm gonna have to start charging
an entrance fee. Oh, God!

748
01:09:33,602 --> 01:09:34,830
Get down!

749
01:09:42,944 --> 01:09:45,173
- Look out!
- Shit!

750
01:09:57,690 --> 01:09:59,248
- You all right?
- Fine.

751
01:10:04,895 --> 01:10:06,194
Shit!

752
01:10:09,301 --> 01:10:10,631
Hold on!

753
01:10:20,744 --> 01:10:22,144
Hold on!

754
01:10:33,422 --> 01:10:34,650
Come on.

755
01:10:42,161 --> 01:10:44,356
- Everyone all right, huh?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

756
01:10:44,564 --> 01:10:45,996
Let me see that. You okay?

757
01:10:46,165 --> 01:10:47,222
- Yeah.
- All right.

758
01:10:49,868 --> 01:10:52,862
Quietly, now. Quietly.

759
01:11:14,023 --> 01:11:15,456
Come on.

760
01:11:36,750 --> 01:11:40,913
Kamajors. Local militia
protecting their homes, huh?

761
01:11:41,087 --> 01:11:42,951
- Do not look them in the eye.
- No.

762
01:11:57,433 --> 01:11:58,923
Excuse me. Excuse me?

763
01:11:59,868 --> 01:12:03,235
<i>Hi, I'm Maddy Bowen
with Vital Affairs magazine.</i>

764
01:12:03,405 --> 01:12:06,463
Wonder if I could take your picture.
I'm just gonna get my camera.

765
01:12:06,641 --> 01:12:09,576
I've heard about your struggle.
I'd love to know more about it.

766
01:12:09,744 --> 01:12:12,372
Would you mind if I took your picture?
Everyone together?

767
01:12:12,714 --> 01:12:14,477
Everyone could all come in together.

768
01:12:17,985 --> 01:12:20,010
Is that okay?
If everyone could come closer.

769
01:12:21,054 --> 01:12:24,147
If you come over here and come in
nice and close. That's good.

770
01:12:24,323 --> 01:12:27,780
Yeah. That's great.
And we'll get one with all of us.

771
01:12:28,059 --> 01:12:29,857
There you go. That's perfect.

772
01:12:31,663 --> 01:12:34,188
How about one together?
Us together, what do you think?

773
01:12:34,366 --> 01:12:36,334
I'll come in like this, yeah?

774
01:12:37,135 --> 01:12:38,124
Cheese.

775
01:12:40,305 --> 01:12:42,636
So do you think
they've read your work?

776
01:12:42,806 --> 01:12:44,934
Shut up.

777
01:12:57,819 --> 01:13:00,152
Hey, get them, get them, get them.

778
01:13:01,791 --> 01:13:05,488
- I got a score. I got a score.
- You missed.

779
01:13:06,195 --> 01:13:08,355
Where have you come from?

780
01:13:08,929 --> 01:13:11,659
- Where did you come from?
- Where have you come from?

781
01:13:12,767 --> 01:13:15,600
That's right. Yeah.
From New York. From America.

782
01:13:15,768 --> 01:13:17,668
I don't have anything for you.

783
01:13:37,988 --> 01:13:39,784
My name is Benjamin Margai.

784
01:13:40,490 --> 01:13:42,548
Danny Archer. This is Maddy Bowen.

785
01:13:42,725 --> 01:13:45,785
- Hello. How are you?
- Very well, thank you.

786
01:14:00,607 --> 01:14:02,904
I'm the cameraman?

787
01:14:05,513 --> 01:14:08,447
The Belgians were the first
to chop off limbs in Africa.

788
01:14:08,615 --> 01:14:12,983
King Leopold took one hand
for every hundredth slave in the Congo...

789
01:14:13,152 --> 01:14:15,245
...to keep them in line.

790
01:14:15,888 --> 01:14:18,822
Many of these children
were taken by the RUF.

791
01:14:18,990 --> 01:14:20,982
We have taken them back.

792
01:14:21,160 --> 01:14:24,254
Some of them have been
made to do horrible things.

793
01:14:24,430 --> 01:14:27,454
We are trying
to bring them back to life.

794
01:14:27,632 --> 01:14:29,258
Let me show you.

795
01:14:31,301 --> 01:14:33,600
Imagine doing all this, huh?

796
01:14:34,905 --> 01:14:36,802
What's your excuse?

797
01:14:37,606 --> 01:14:42,942
Well, it's gotten hard to go back
to sipping lattes and talking interest rates.

798
01:14:43,178 --> 01:14:45,804
So you're an action junkie, huh?

799
01:14:46,747 --> 01:14:49,045
Three out of five ex-boyfriends
recently polled...

800
01:14:49,216 --> 01:14:53,653
...say that I prefer to be
in a constant state of crisis.

801
01:14:54,187 --> 01:14:56,451
Maybe I just give a shit.

802
01:15:00,126 --> 01:15:01,115
You were good today.

803
01:15:03,561 --> 01:15:04,892
You know that?

804
01:15:06,031 --> 01:15:07,522
You too.

805
01:15:10,468 --> 01:15:13,403
"--that sometimes they forgot
to close the door.

806
01:15:13,571 --> 01:15:16,631
She also wrote
about her sister Josie...

807
01:15:17,242 --> 01:15:22,234
...who was very ill
and who had to be taken to hospital."

808
01:15:24,281 --> 01:15:25,475
Cheers.

809
01:15:28,284 --> 01:15:30,878
So how many attacks
have there been in the area?

810
01:15:31,053 --> 01:15:33,955
I have known most of the rebels
since they were children.

811
01:15:34,123 --> 01:15:38,651
The local commander is still afraid
I will come after him with my ruler.

812
01:15:40,096 --> 01:15:43,554
So you think because your intentions
are good, they'll spare you, huh?

813
01:15:43,733 --> 01:15:46,564
My heart always told me
that people are inherently good.

814
01:15:46,734 --> 01:15:48,930
My experience suggests otherwise.

815
01:15:49,104 --> 01:15:50,900
But what about you, Mr. Archer?

816
01:15:51,338 --> 01:15:53,773
In your long career as a journalist...

817
01:15:53,941 --> 01:15:56,772
...would you say that people
are mostly good?

818
01:15:58,844 --> 01:16:00,277
No.

819
01:16:00,545 --> 01:16:02,070
I'd say they're just people.

820
01:16:02,247 --> 01:16:06,181
Exactly. It is what they do
that makes them good or bad.

821
01:16:06,349 --> 01:16:09,580
A moment of love,
even in a bad man...

822
01:16:09,853 --> 01:16:12,322
...can give meaning to a life.

823
01:16:12,490 --> 01:16:16,118
None of us knows which path
will lead us to God.

824
01:16:18,862 --> 01:16:20,352
Hey!

825
01:17:08,340 --> 01:17:10,204
It's palm wine.

826
01:17:19,481 --> 01:17:22,416
- Jesus Christ.
- Yeah, yeah. It takes getting used to, huh?

827
01:17:22,584 --> 01:17:24,072
God.

828
01:17:24,252 --> 01:17:26,982
- Drank that as a boy.
- In Rhodesia?

829
01:17:29,155 --> 01:17:30,384
I take notes.

830
01:17:33,093 --> 01:17:34,822
The Shona...

831
01:17:36,129 --> 01:17:38,427
The Shona have a word for me.

832
01:17:40,267 --> 01:17:43,895
- It means "white boy in Africa."
- When did you leave?

833
01:17:44,535 --> 01:17:46,232
I didn't leave.

834
01:17:46,405 --> 01:17:50,739
<i>I got sent away to South Africa
in 1978 when the munts overran us.</i>

835
01:17:51,075 --> 01:17:52,542
Then you joined the army?

836
01:17:55,413 --> 01:17:57,573
Yeah. Yeah, I did my time in Angola.

837
01:17:57,749 --> 01:18:00,444
- The 32 Battalion.
- That's right.

838
01:18:02,820 --> 01:18:06,084
You know, contrary to what
you might think about us...

839
01:18:06,256 --> 01:18:09,747
...we fought with the blacks, huh?
Yeah. Side by side.

840
01:18:09,926 --> 01:18:13,658
There was no apartheid in a foxhole.
The colonel always used to tell us that.

841
01:18:13,830 --> 01:18:17,229
- This is Colonel Coetzee?
- Yeah.

842
01:18:19,467 --> 01:18:22,868
Then, of course, it's 1994.
No more army.

843
01:18:23,039 --> 01:18:24,869
No more apartheid.

844
01:18:25,039 --> 01:18:28,406
Truth and reconciliation
and all of that rubbish, you know.

845
01:18:28,575 --> 01:18:30,065
Kumbaya.

846
01:18:30,844 --> 01:18:33,606
We fought and died together,
you know?

847
01:18:33,778 --> 01:18:37,045
Black and white. Most people back home
didn't even know we were at war.

848
01:18:37,215 --> 01:18:39,080
We thought we were
fighting Communism...

849
01:18:39,251 --> 01:18:43,117
...but in the end, it was all about
who gets what, you know?

850
01:18:43,286 --> 01:18:46,347
Ivory, oil, gold:

851
01:18:47,290 --> 01:18:49,053
Diamonds.

852
01:18:52,295 --> 01:18:55,264
So one day I decided,
"Fuck it," you know?

853
01:18:55,899 --> 01:18:57,456
"I'm gonna get mine."

854
01:18:57,634 --> 01:18:59,225
You gonna steal his diamond?

855
01:19:06,742 --> 01:19:10,438
That diamond is my ticket
out of this godforsaken continent.

856
01:19:10,645 --> 01:19:12,476
That doesn't answer the question.

857
01:19:23,124 --> 01:19:27,218
My dad came home
from the war in '69.

858
01:19:29,495 --> 01:19:31,360
And it took him...

859
01:19:32,498 --> 01:19:34,590
...about 20 years to get right.

860
01:19:36,468 --> 01:19:37,766
What?

861
01:19:40,639 --> 01:19:44,937
You Americans love to talk
about your feelings, huh?

862
01:19:45,109 --> 01:19:47,374
So, what does that mean?
What does that mean?

863
01:19:47,545 --> 01:19:49,671
- Got a thing for messed-up vets now?
- Shut up.

864
01:19:51,683 --> 01:19:53,146
You lost both your parents.

865
01:19:54,049 --> 01:19:56,882
That's a polite way
of putting it, yeah.

866
01:19:59,521 --> 01:20:01,852
Mom was raped and shot...

867
01:20:04,691 --> 01:20:07,785
...and Dad was decapitated
and hung from a hook in the barn.

868
01:20:09,330 --> 01:20:11,058
I was 9.

869
01:20:14,667 --> 01:20:16,259
Boohoo, right?

870
01:20:20,005 --> 01:20:22,131
Sometimes I wonder...

871
01:20:25,244 --> 01:20:28,304
...will God ever forgive us
for what we've done to each other?

872
01:20:31,949 --> 01:20:34,816
Then I look around and I realize...

873
01:20:35,720 --> 01:20:39,177
...God left this place a long time ago.

874
01:20:45,896 --> 01:20:47,921
It's...

875
01:20:50,199 --> 01:20:52,133
What's the point, huh?

876
01:21:35,572 --> 01:21:37,597
Oh, shit. Keep moving, huh?

877
01:21:37,774 --> 01:21:39,536
- What?
- Drive at them. They'll panic.

878
01:21:39,708 --> 01:21:41,972
Do you know where the word
"infantry" comes from?

879
01:21:42,144 --> 01:21:45,443
It means "child soldier."
They are just children.

880
01:21:45,614 --> 01:21:49,276
- Stop! Stop! RUF on the road!
- Hi. Hello. Hello.

881
01:21:50,518 --> 01:21:51,576
Hello, little brothers.

882
01:21:51,752 --> 01:21:54,277
- RUF on the road!
- Yeah, yeah. What is your names?

883
01:21:54,788 --> 01:21:57,086
I'm Dead Body.
Who is this motherfucker?

884
01:21:57,257 --> 01:21:58,917
We are teachers on our way to Kono.

885
01:21:59,091 --> 01:22:01,322
Only RUF on the road.

886
01:22:01,496 --> 01:22:03,429
- RUF only!
- Yes, yes, I understand that.

887
01:22:03,630 --> 01:22:04,960
- Only RUF!
- But son, this is--

888
01:22:07,234 --> 01:22:08,824
Don't move! Don't move! Fuck.

889
01:22:11,070 --> 01:22:14,401
Jesus Christ! Maddy, press your hand
against the exit wound there, huh?

890
01:22:14,572 --> 01:22:16,871
- Got it.
- Keep it there, huh?

891
01:22:17,042 --> 01:22:18,804
Whatever you do,
don't talk, all right?

892
01:22:18,977 --> 01:22:20,809
Is there any wine left in that jug?

893
01:22:20,979 --> 01:22:22,843
- Here.
- Pour it all over everything, huh?

894
01:22:24,381 --> 01:22:27,316
The colonel's gonna have a medic
at the airstrip in Kono.

895
01:22:27,483 --> 01:22:30,477
- How far is it?
- You said not to talk.

896
01:22:30,755 --> 01:22:31,945
A comedian, huh?

897
01:22:46,132 --> 01:22:48,533
- How's his pulse?
- I can feel it sometimes.

898
01:22:58,977 --> 01:23:01,945
- Hold it right there.
- Stop.

899
01:23:02,113 --> 01:23:03,343
Papers, please.

900
01:23:07,518 --> 01:23:08,746
Excuse me.

901
01:23:08,920 --> 01:23:11,855
I was just trying
to keep pressure on the wound.

902
01:23:12,023 --> 01:23:14,548
- He's lost a lot of blood.
- You'll be all right, huh?

903
01:23:15,226 --> 01:23:16,522
Will you?

904
01:23:17,227 --> 01:23:20,220
I'll check on him in the tent
in a little bit. Thank you.

905
01:23:20,463 --> 01:23:21,795
Hey.

906
01:23:22,333 --> 01:23:24,322
Look who's alive, eh?

907
01:23:24,500 --> 01:23:25,832
I told the H you'd be back.

908
01:23:27,803 --> 01:23:30,738
I'm afraid we're evacuating
all non-military personnel, miss.

909
01:23:30,906 --> 01:23:32,736
Transport touches down at 1600.

910
01:23:32,907 --> 01:23:34,670
She's with me, all right?

911
01:23:34,877 --> 01:23:38,539
No exceptions, pal. This is gonna be ugly.
Colonel doesn't want an audience.

912
01:23:38,714 --> 01:23:41,511
Is I.R.'s presence here
known to other African nations?

913
01:23:43,016 --> 01:23:45,041
- She's with you?
- Yeah.

914
01:23:46,186 --> 01:23:48,051
Come on. The colonel's this way.

915
01:23:48,222 --> 01:23:50,054
Give me a minute, huh?

916
01:23:53,225 --> 01:23:55,749
We block their escape
by blowing the bridge.

917
01:23:57,395 --> 01:23:59,089
That's correct.

918
01:23:59,830 --> 01:24:02,128
You made it out. Well done.

919
01:24:02,332 --> 01:24:04,267
Negative, Kilo Foxtrot, stand by.

920
01:24:04,934 --> 01:24:08,598
- Colonel, sir.
- So must be real, then.

921
01:24:09,772 --> 01:24:10,966
The pink.

922
01:24:11,474 --> 01:24:14,068
Well, you're part
of this operation now.

923
01:24:14,244 --> 01:24:17,734
First we snuff everything that moves
out there, then we find your diamond.

924
01:24:17,913 --> 01:24:19,539
Colonel?

925
01:24:20,081 --> 01:24:22,517
Go get kitted. Yes?

926
01:24:28,822 --> 01:24:30,814
Move, move, move!

927
01:24:31,025 --> 01:24:34,289
- Go get your kit.
- Will do, chum. Will do.

928
01:24:37,830 --> 01:24:40,994
It's go time, all right?
Meet me behind the tents.

929
01:24:44,104 --> 01:24:45,798
How's Benjamin?

930
01:24:45,972 --> 01:24:47,438
They say he'll live.

931
01:24:48,774 --> 01:24:50,036
Good. Good.

932
01:24:57,448 --> 01:24:59,246
Listen, Maddy...

933
01:25:00,653 --> 01:25:02,414
...I need you to do me one last favor.

934
01:25:03,453 --> 01:25:04,819
Yeah?

935
01:25:06,790 --> 01:25:08,451
Tell that guard
you wanna put him...

936
01:25:08,625 --> 01:25:11,285
<i>...on the cover of Soldier of Fortune
magazine for me.</i>

937
01:25:17,331 --> 01:25:18,560
You're going in.

938
01:25:22,969 --> 01:25:25,233
You and Solomon.

939
01:25:27,408 --> 01:25:28,396
You're going in now.

940
01:25:29,242 --> 01:25:31,437
Your plane leaves
in a few minutes, huh?

941
01:25:34,046 --> 01:25:36,014
You're an idiot.

942
01:25:40,319 --> 01:25:43,186
- What if I wanted to go in with you?
- I'd say no.

943
01:25:43,355 --> 01:25:45,346
- What if I insist?
- I'd insist back.

944
01:25:51,462 --> 01:25:52,655
It's my story.

945
01:25:52,829 --> 01:25:56,230
Your story is Van De Kaap, all right?
That stone is mine.

946
01:25:56,399 --> 01:25:59,836
I'm not leaving here without it,
you understand?

947
01:26:01,305 --> 01:26:04,170
Please, just give me two minutes.

948
01:26:20,921 --> 01:26:22,320
Yeah.

949
01:26:33,631 --> 01:26:35,326
- Hello.
- Hi.

950
01:26:35,500 --> 01:26:38,730
<i>My name is Maddy Bowen.
I'm with Vital Affairs magazine.</i>

951
01:26:38,901 --> 01:26:41,369
I was wondering
if I could ask you a few questions.

952
01:26:41,537 --> 01:26:43,062
Well, that depends what they are.

953
01:26:43,239 --> 01:26:47,199
Oh, I see you're familiar
with our devious ways, aren't you?

954
01:26:47,944 --> 01:26:49,844
Okay, so I'll start
with something simple.

955
01:27:02,457 --> 01:27:05,119
And before that you were with
the South African Defense--?

956
01:27:05,292 --> 01:27:06,953
- Defense Force, correct.
- Of course.

957
01:27:07,128 --> 01:27:10,565
And was that with Colonel Coetzee?
Were you in Angola?

958
01:27:10,732 --> 01:27:12,254
Angola, yeah.

959
01:27:13,867 --> 01:27:16,835
That is all I really need to know.
Thank you so much.

960
01:27:17,035 --> 01:27:18,504
- Thank you.
- Okay.

961
01:27:28,514 --> 01:27:29,913
Thank you, huh?

962
01:27:30,082 --> 01:27:32,515
Just keeping my end of the deal.

963
01:27:33,118 --> 01:27:34,415
Good luck to you, Solomon.

964
01:27:34,720 --> 01:27:36,209
Okay.

965
01:27:37,388 --> 01:27:41,221
- I hope you find what you're looking for.
- Thank you for all you have done.

966
01:27:48,665 --> 01:27:51,257
- Listen, I--
- No, you listen.

967
01:27:55,870 --> 01:27:57,769
In another life maybe, all right?

968
01:27:59,206 --> 01:28:01,037
Yeah. Sure.

969
01:28:01,208 --> 01:28:02,573
Yeah.

970
01:28:06,914 --> 01:28:09,040
You find yourself a good man,
all right, Maddy?

971
01:28:14,987 --> 01:28:18,012
You know, I've got three sisters.

972
01:28:18,189 --> 01:28:20,819
They're all married to good men.

973
01:28:22,694 --> 01:28:23,752
I prefer my life.

974
01:28:26,397 --> 01:28:30,857
Here is my office phone...

975
01:28:31,035 --> 01:28:33,400
...home phone, cellphone.

976
01:28:35,505 --> 01:28:38,669
I'm used to being pursued,
but what the heck.

977
01:28:49,852 --> 01:28:51,978
You better get on that plane, huh?

978
01:28:53,722 --> 01:28:55,621
You should get on that plane.

979
01:29:03,797 --> 01:29:05,594
So should you.

980
01:29:12,070 --> 01:29:13,195
You gonna call me?

981
01:29:17,008 --> 01:29:18,497
Soon as I'm near a phone, yeah.

982
01:29:19,443 --> 01:29:21,809
Yeah, right.

983
01:29:43,631 --> 01:29:46,896
- Where is he?
- I don't know.

984
01:29:51,472 --> 01:29:53,063
Oh, shit.

985
01:29:53,339 --> 01:29:56,070
Nabil? Yeah, I'll call you
when we get closer, all right?

986
01:29:56,242 --> 01:29:58,837
You keep me posted. Right.

987
01:29:59,013 --> 01:30:02,811
All right. I set the pace, huh?
Two-hour marches, five-minute breaks.

988
01:30:02,981 --> 01:30:06,815
If I hold my hand up like this, you stop.
If I point to the dirt, you lie flat.

989
01:30:06,985 --> 01:30:10,544
If I say go, you move like your life
depended on it. Understood?

990
01:30:10,720 --> 01:30:13,384
- Yes, boss.
- Come on.

991
01:30:23,667 --> 01:30:25,328
Tell me about the stone.

992
01:30:25,502 --> 01:30:28,127
Is it clear or is it milky?

993
01:30:28,302 --> 01:30:29,827
Clear.

994
01:30:30,004 --> 01:30:32,404
And the color, is it strong?

995
01:30:32,573 --> 01:30:33,801
Does it hold the light?

996
01:30:33,974 --> 01:30:36,034
It is as you say.

997
01:30:36,476 --> 01:30:39,638
- About the size of a bird's egg?
- Yes.

998
01:30:39,813 --> 01:30:43,977
One hundred carats.
Come on, let's pick up the pace.

999
01:31:25,554 --> 01:31:26,919
Dia!

1000
01:31:28,823 --> 01:31:30,791
Stop the truck!

1001
01:31:31,560 --> 01:31:33,254
I thought it was Dia.

1002
01:32:27,175 --> 01:32:28,732
Wake up.

1003
01:32:30,576 --> 01:32:33,670
Don't worry, they're gone, huh?

1004
01:32:35,014 --> 01:32:38,143
You know, I once had this buddy...

1005
01:32:38,317 --> 01:32:40,182
...named Mabhoko.

1006
01:32:40,952 --> 01:32:44,183
We used to hunt bush meat
together as kids, huh?

1007
01:32:44,990 --> 01:32:46,355
Baboons.

1008
01:32:46,525 --> 01:32:49,390
Baboons, they were
the hardest to catch. They're...

1009
01:32:50,495 --> 01:32:51,826
They're cunning.

1010
01:32:51,997 --> 01:32:54,089
Cunning creatures.

1011
01:32:54,366 --> 01:32:56,993
Fast, strong.

1012
01:32:57,168 --> 01:32:59,397
Got good eyesight.

1013
01:32:59,904 --> 01:33:03,930
We would always find them
by the smell of their shit.

1014
01:33:04,107 --> 01:33:09,236
And that's how we learned to track
your black terrorists in Angola, huh?

1015
01:33:13,314 --> 01:33:14,747
By the smell of your shit.

1016
01:33:15,781 --> 01:33:17,248
It's not...

1017
01:33:17,416 --> 01:33:20,146
It's not the same as a baboon's.

1018
01:33:22,389 --> 01:33:25,949
But, you know, after you skin it...

1019
01:33:27,259 --> 01:33:29,489
...the flesh of a baboon...

1020
01:33:29,762 --> 01:33:32,162
...isn't that much different
than a man's, you know.

1021
01:33:35,566 --> 01:33:39,503
I'll tell you, I can track anything.

1022
01:33:51,748 --> 01:33:53,908
You risk my life like that again...

1023
01:33:59,287 --> 01:34:01,415
...and I'll peel your face
back off your head.

1024
01:34:03,925 --> 01:34:06,190
Do you understand?

1025
01:34:14,435 --> 01:34:16,494
Make us a fire.

1026
01:35:26,765 --> 01:35:28,356
What'd he say?

1027
01:35:28,532 --> 01:35:30,660
We are going the right way.

1028
01:35:37,808 --> 01:35:40,537
Hold up there, my man.
It's this way, huh?

1029
01:35:42,011 --> 01:35:44,207
Where do you think you are going?

1030
01:35:45,879 --> 01:35:47,541
Stop!

1031
01:35:47,815 --> 01:35:49,510
I said, stop!

1032
01:35:49,951 --> 01:35:51,508
He is not down there, all right?

1033
01:35:53,554 --> 01:35:57,216
All right. You're gonna need
some of that old discipline, huh?

1034
01:35:57,390 --> 01:35:59,653
Now you listen here, my boy,
and you listen well.

1035
01:35:59,825 --> 01:36:01,794
You are not going down there.
Are we clear?

1036
01:36:01,963 --> 01:36:03,588
You are not the master.

1037
01:36:03,762 --> 01:36:07,391
Right now, that is exactly what I am,
and you'd better remember it, Kaffir!

1038
01:36:22,546 --> 01:36:23,877
Don't you fucking move, huh?

1039
01:36:24,047 --> 01:36:26,015
Don't you move. Don't you move, huh?

1040
01:36:26,184 --> 01:36:28,515
- My son is there!
- Your son is gone!

1041
01:36:28,684 --> 01:36:30,015
- He is alive!
- He's gone!

1042
01:36:30,186 --> 01:36:32,747
He's alive! He's there
with those crazy people!

1043
01:36:33,957 --> 01:36:37,393
I am his father! His father!
I should have protected him!

1044
01:36:37,860 --> 01:36:41,761
I must go find him.
I cannot live without knowing!

1045
01:36:41,929 --> 01:36:44,160
Shoot me if you want, but I'm going.

1046
01:36:46,267 --> 01:36:49,726
Why should it matter,
I'm dead already.

1047
01:36:57,577 --> 01:36:59,841
We wait until dark, huh?

1048
01:37:29,004 --> 01:37:30,402
Are you satisfied?

1049
01:37:33,373 --> 01:37:35,898
All right, come on.

1050
01:37:40,647 --> 01:37:42,842
<i>--is fighting for Sierra Leone</i>

1051
01:37:43,016 --> 01:37:46,076
<i>RUF is fighting for Sierra Leone</i>

1052
01:37:46,253 --> 01:37:49,186
<i>Go tell my parents
They may see me no more</i>

1053
01:37:49,355 --> 01:37:52,415
<i>In the battlefield
We're fighting forever</i>

1054
01:37:52,591 --> 01:37:55,493
<i>Go tell my parents
They may see me no more</i>

1055
01:37:55,662 --> 01:37:57,128
<i>In the battlefield...</i>

1056
01:37:59,699 --> 01:38:01,666
You are how old?

1057
01:38:01,833 --> 01:38:03,596
Me? I'm 31.

1058
01:38:03,768 --> 01:38:05,928
And you have no wife?

1059
01:38:06,403 --> 01:38:09,271
- No.
- No children?

1060
01:38:10,441 --> 01:38:11,739
No.

1061
01:38:11,910 --> 01:38:13,537
And no home?

1062
01:38:13,712 --> 01:38:15,371
No.

1063
01:38:16,079 --> 01:38:18,480
But you have money, yes?

1064
01:38:18,649 --> 01:38:20,912
Yeah, some.

1065
01:38:21,084 --> 01:38:23,076
But not enough?

1066
01:38:25,585 --> 01:38:27,144
No.

1067
01:38:27,888 --> 01:38:32,382
If you get this diamond,
you will have enough money, yes?

1068
01:38:34,526 --> 01:38:35,550
Yes.

1069
01:38:35,728 --> 01:38:38,526
Then you will get
a wife and children?

1070
01:38:38,696 --> 01:38:40,097
Probably not, no.

1071
01:38:42,167 --> 01:38:43,155
What?

1072
01:38:45,270 --> 01:38:46,794
What?

1073
01:38:47,206 --> 01:38:49,265
I am confused.

1074
01:38:50,341 --> 01:38:51,808
Yeah?

1075
01:38:51,975 --> 01:38:54,774
<i>That makes two of us, my bru.</i>

1076
01:38:57,281 --> 01:39:00,772
Oh, Christ.
I've gotta quit smoking, huh?

1077
01:39:01,385 --> 01:39:03,353
Why don't you?

1078
01:39:03,620 --> 01:39:06,020
I'll tell you what, Solomon.

1079
01:39:06,288 --> 01:39:10,815
You find me this diamond,
and I'll quit right then and there, huh?

1080
01:39:18,234 --> 01:39:21,225
- You were born in Zimbabwe?
- Oh, yeah.

1081
01:39:21,403 --> 01:39:24,566
- Is it beautiful there?
- Sure you're not a reporter?

1082
01:39:24,973 --> 01:39:28,431
Because you ask a hell of a lot
of questions, my man.

1083
01:39:36,082 --> 01:39:39,779
My grandfather told
many stories of war.

1084
01:39:40,019 --> 01:39:42,852
How the Mende fought the Temne.

1085
01:39:43,022 --> 01:39:46,751
Or how two tribes would fight
when somebody had stolen a woman.

1086
01:39:56,833 --> 01:40:00,201
I understand white people
want our diamonds, yes?

1087
01:40:03,238 --> 01:40:06,968
But how can my own people
do this to each other?

1088
01:40:15,250 --> 01:40:17,308
I know good people...

1089
01:40:17,485 --> 01:40:20,351
...who say there is something
wrong with us...

1090
01:40:20,720 --> 01:40:21,880
...inside our black skin.

1091
01:40:22,055 --> 01:40:25,388
That we were better off
when the white man ruled.

1092
01:40:27,293 --> 01:40:30,090
But my son is good.

1093
01:40:31,664 --> 01:40:33,860
And when he grows up...

1094
01:40:34,034 --> 01:40:35,261
...and peace comes...

1095
01:40:39,270 --> 01:40:41,932
...this place will be a paradise.

1096
01:40:49,814 --> 01:40:52,281
We'll get your son back, huh?

1097
01:41:33,984 --> 01:41:36,317
Where is it exactly?

1098
01:41:37,854 --> 01:41:40,754
Through the camp, by the river.

1099
01:41:45,361 --> 01:41:47,056
Christ.

1100
01:41:47,530 --> 01:41:49,157
Okay.

1101
01:41:49,797 --> 01:41:51,663
I'm gonna make contact
with the colonel.

1102
01:41:51,834 --> 01:41:53,359
He'll send in an air strike.

1103
01:41:53,803 --> 01:41:56,771
- What is that?
- A chopper, huh? An attack helicopter.

1104
01:41:56,939 --> 01:41:59,462
- We use it as a diversion.
- What if my son is there?

1105
01:41:59,641 --> 01:42:00,938
- He isn't.
- How do you know?

1106
01:42:01,109 --> 01:42:04,703
I said we do it my way now, all right?
Don't fuck with me.

1107
01:42:14,621 --> 01:42:17,020
Cordell, it's Danny.

1108
01:42:17,190 --> 01:42:19,522
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Shut up and listen, all right?

1109
01:42:19,692 --> 01:42:22,556
You tell the colonel I've found the stone.

1110
01:42:22,725 --> 01:42:25,696
No, I haven't got it in my hands,
but I'm OP'ing its location.

1111
01:42:25,863 --> 01:42:27,454
It's a major rebel camp, my man.

1112
01:42:27,631 --> 01:42:29,997
You tell him to send in the dakadak.

1113
01:42:30,568 --> 01:42:33,434
Because I stole a GPS, that's how.

1114
01:42:33,602 --> 01:42:36,162
If you shut up and listen,
I could give the coordinates.

1115
01:42:36,605 --> 01:42:39,631
Zero-nine-zero-five-four-two-four, north.

1116
01:42:39,809 --> 01:42:44,371
Three-two-seven-two-nine
three-zero-five-zero, east.

1117
01:42:44,546 --> 01:42:46,809
I'll call back at midnight to confirm.

1118
01:42:49,584 --> 01:42:52,518
You can look all night,
my friend, right?

1119
01:42:52,686 --> 01:42:55,349
I promise you he is not there.

1120
01:43:00,594 --> 01:43:02,789
They're coming in the morning, all right?

1121
01:43:02,963 --> 01:43:05,397
No movement, my friend. You stay still.

1122
01:43:07,333 --> 01:43:09,768
When it gets dark,
then we move in closer.

1123
01:43:31,923 --> 01:43:34,914
Solomon. Shit.

1124
01:43:45,699 --> 01:43:47,098
I can do it.

1125
01:43:47,268 --> 01:43:48,360
- Help me.
- Help him.

1126
01:43:48,534 --> 01:43:50,593
Thank you, Papa.

1127
01:44:32,542 --> 01:44:34,770
Hey, you smell.

1128
01:44:35,977 --> 01:44:37,444
That's fine.

1129
01:44:49,757 --> 01:44:51,724
- Ready? I'm winning.
- Okay, let's go.

1130
01:44:51,891 --> 01:44:53,552
Play, man.

1131
01:44:55,128 --> 01:44:58,028
- Play. Play the card.
- Play.

1132
01:45:24,819 --> 01:45:25,946
Dia.

1133
01:45:28,988 --> 01:45:30,684
Leave me alone.

1134
01:45:31,726 --> 01:45:34,957
- Dia. I'm your papa. Come with me.
- Hey.

1135
01:45:35,129 --> 01:45:36,857
- Dia.
- Get away from me.

1136
01:45:37,030 --> 01:45:38,826
- Dia. Dia!
- I do not know you. Traitor!

1137
01:45:39,199 --> 01:45:41,690
- Enemy! Enemy!
- What the hell are you doing?

1138
01:45:41,869 --> 01:45:43,096
- What are you doing?
- I don't know you!

1139
01:45:43,268 --> 01:45:44,566
- What's wrong?
- I hate you!

1140
01:45:44,738 --> 01:45:46,466
- Dia, come with me!
- I hate you!

1141
01:45:46,638 --> 01:45:48,161
Get away from me!

1142
01:45:50,643 --> 01:45:52,507
- Get him!
- Don't shoot!

1143
01:45:53,012 --> 01:45:55,241
- Don't shoot! Don't--! Don't shoot!
- I hate you!

1144
01:45:55,413 --> 01:45:57,313
- Fisherman! Traitor!
- Don't shoot!

1145
01:45:57,481 --> 01:45:59,712
Get away from me!

1146
01:46:06,823 --> 01:46:08,985
I knew you would come back.

1147
01:46:09,460 --> 01:46:12,950
I have dug and dug and dug,
but I've found nothing.

1148
01:46:13,129 --> 01:46:15,030
Nothing.

1149
01:46:15,297 --> 01:46:16,787
Dig, dig, dig!

1150
01:46:16,966 --> 01:46:19,265
You will find it for me.

1151
01:46:20,234 --> 01:46:22,532
You will dig up
what you have come back for.

1152
01:46:22,703 --> 01:46:23,727
No.

1153
01:46:23,904 --> 01:46:26,337
Why should the diamond
go to the foreign devils?

1154
01:46:27,074 --> 01:46:30,338
We will use it
to make the country strong.

1155
01:46:30,809 --> 01:46:33,404
RUF is fighting for the people!

1156
01:46:35,747 --> 01:46:38,841
RUF is fighting for Sierra Leone!

1157
01:46:41,686 --> 01:46:43,415
Pick it up.

1158
01:46:44,623 --> 01:46:47,591
Why? You are going to kill me anyway.

1159
01:46:47,758 --> 01:46:50,851
I do not need to kill you,
Solomon Vandy.

1160
01:46:53,697 --> 01:46:55,891
If you do not bring me the diamond...

1161
01:46:56,065 --> 01:46:58,294
...I will find the rest of your family.

1162
01:46:58,468 --> 01:47:00,902
Just as I have found your son.

1163
01:47:02,005 --> 01:47:05,371
I will rape your wife
in front of your eyes...

1164
01:47:06,175 --> 01:47:08,473
...slit her throat...

1165
01:47:09,078 --> 01:47:11,443
...and I will keep your daughters
for myself.

1166
01:47:16,850 --> 01:47:19,285
You think I am a devil...

1167
01:47:19,454 --> 01:47:21,785
...but only because I have lived in hell.

1168
01:47:23,423 --> 01:47:26,085
I want to get out.

1169
01:47:26,694 --> 01:47:28,787
You will help me.

1170
01:47:31,630 --> 01:47:32,928
I don't remember.

1171
01:47:33,099 --> 01:47:36,067
Find it or your family will die!

1172
01:47:37,002 --> 01:47:38,868
Now pick it up!

1173
01:47:54,416 --> 01:47:55,850
- Go!
- Bastards!

1174
01:47:56,018 --> 01:47:57,383
Shoot it!

1175
01:48:02,357 --> 01:48:03,345
Dia!

1176
01:48:15,435 --> 01:48:17,629
Come, boy. Come. This way. This way.

1177
01:48:18,505 --> 01:48:19,733
Dia!

1178
01:48:42,626 --> 01:48:44,219
<i>Colonel, we think Archer's there.</i>

1179
01:48:44,395 --> 01:48:47,227
I don't give a damn who's down there.
Kill them all.

1180
01:48:57,573 --> 01:48:58,833
Dia!

1181
01:49:13,585 --> 01:49:14,883
I'm coming!

1182
01:49:18,423 --> 01:49:20,084
- Dia!
- Bastard!

1183
01:49:43,245 --> 01:49:44,610
No!

1184
01:50:04,698 --> 01:50:06,030
Dia!

1185
01:51:12,256 --> 01:51:15,191
- We found his digger, sir.
- Keep him close.

1186
01:51:17,161 --> 01:51:19,355
- Danny boy.
- Colonel.

1187
01:51:19,529 --> 01:51:22,897
- Thanks for calling it in.
- Yeah, yeah. Always happy to help, huh?

1188
01:51:23,067 --> 01:51:26,400
So where is it? The stone?

1189
01:51:26,570 --> 01:51:28,503
We split, huh? Fifty-fifty, all right?

1190
01:51:28,672 --> 01:51:30,299
Look around you, Danny boy.

1191
01:51:30,472 --> 01:51:33,441
You're not in a position
to be dictating terms.

1192
01:51:33,609 --> 01:51:35,703
Then you will never find it, sir.

1193
01:51:35,879 --> 01:51:37,505
That's correct.

1194
01:51:39,179 --> 01:51:41,807
- But he will.
- Come. Up.

1195
01:51:43,450 --> 01:51:45,680
Introduce me to your digger.

1196
01:51:47,252 --> 01:51:48,914
Solomon Vandy.

1197
01:51:49,088 --> 01:51:51,249
This is Colonel Coetzee.
He wants the diamond.

1198
01:51:51,423 --> 01:51:54,451
- No more than you.
- Fuck.

1199
01:51:54,627 --> 01:51:56,617
You gonna show us where it's hidden?

1200
01:51:59,297 --> 01:52:00,992
Does he speak English?

1201
01:52:01,166 --> 01:52:04,191
He will only tell me, sir.
I promise you that.

1202
01:52:05,035 --> 01:52:08,094
- Let me talk to him, huh?
- Go on.

1203
01:52:14,844 --> 01:52:17,210
All right, my friend.

1204
01:52:17,380 --> 01:52:19,314
End of the line here, huh?

1205
01:52:19,482 --> 01:52:22,746
- You just tell him where it is, all right?
- I do not trust him.

1206
01:52:22,918 --> 01:52:26,355
I don't trust him either,
but we haven't got much of a choice here.

1207
01:52:28,057 --> 01:52:31,183
I promise you
he will shoot us both in the head.

1208
01:52:31,625 --> 01:52:34,388
Right, tell him, huh?
Tell him where it is, huh?

1209
01:52:34,562 --> 01:52:37,156
- Go on. Come on.
- I'm not feeling the love, Danny.

1210
01:52:38,365 --> 01:52:41,198
All right.
No more messing about, all right?

1211
01:52:41,368 --> 01:52:44,359
I said tell him where it is!
Tell him where it is! Now!

1212
01:52:44,537 --> 01:52:46,199
Tell him!

1213
01:52:47,374 --> 01:52:49,169
- No.
- Fucking--

1214
01:52:49,341 --> 01:52:52,037
Danny, there are other ways
to do this, okay?

1215
01:52:52,211 --> 01:52:53,838
Yeah, yeah.

1216
01:53:02,017 --> 01:53:05,010
- If he tells us, do we have a deal, sir?
- Seventy-thirty.

1217
01:53:05,187 --> 01:53:07,586
Sixty-forty. I've already lined up a buyer.

1218
01:53:07,756 --> 01:53:09,418
Agreed.

1219
01:53:14,596 --> 01:53:16,154
Come here.

1220
01:53:18,733 --> 01:53:22,169
This is his son. Vandy will do
whatever you want for his sake, all right?

1221
01:53:22,337 --> 01:53:27,103
Danny, you're a pisser, man. Well done.
Boys, we move out.

1222
01:53:29,877 --> 01:53:32,175
What do you say, Mr. Vandy?

1223
01:53:32,646 --> 01:53:35,546
- You ready to take a walk?
- Come on.

1224
01:53:41,820 --> 01:53:43,412
Come on.

1225
01:53:56,367 --> 01:53:59,459
So who's the buyer?
I'm guessing London.

1226
01:53:59,669 --> 01:54:02,934
Well, they no longer accept
conflict diamonds, huh?

1227
01:54:03,106 --> 01:54:05,575
Wouldn't hurt to interest
some other parties.

1228
01:54:06,110 --> 01:54:09,101
- Start a bidding war.
- What, one war's not enough for you, huh?

1229
01:54:10,046 --> 01:54:11,740
I missed you, Danny.

1230
01:54:12,047 --> 01:54:16,211
See? It is here.
He has tried to find it.

1231
01:54:16,383 --> 01:54:19,078
All right, Mr. Vandy.
Time for you to start digging.

1232
01:54:34,133 --> 01:54:36,396
<i>Hey, boet, have you got a smoke?</i>

1233
01:54:36,868 --> 01:54:38,769
Smoking will kill you.

1234
01:54:39,537 --> 01:54:41,027
Sorry.

1235
01:54:44,107 --> 01:54:46,006
It's all right.

1236
01:54:46,176 --> 01:54:48,304
Time I quit smoking anyway,
huh, Solomon?

1237
01:55:02,824 --> 01:55:04,156
- It's gone.
- What?

1238
01:55:04,326 --> 01:55:06,420
Someone has taken it.

1239
01:55:07,530 --> 01:55:11,294
This is where I buried it.
It isn't here.

1240
01:55:11,766 --> 01:55:15,133
Well, then there's no reason
for any of you to stay alive. Is there?

1241
01:55:19,472 --> 01:55:21,134
Wait, wait, wait.

1242
01:55:21,308 --> 01:55:23,538
I know, I know. I know where it is.

1243
01:55:24,011 --> 01:55:26,002
- I know where it is.
- It better be there.

1244
01:55:31,183 --> 01:55:32,172
Yes.

1245
01:55:32,351 --> 01:55:35,716
Oh, here, here.
It is here.

1246
01:55:35,886 --> 01:55:37,547
- Yeah? Yeah, there it is.
- Yes.

1247
01:55:38,722 --> 01:55:40,121
Fuck!

1248
01:55:58,773 --> 01:56:00,706
TIA, huh, Danny?

1249
01:56:02,110 --> 01:56:03,701
TIA.

1250
01:56:10,617 --> 01:56:14,074
Keep digging, huh?
They'll be here any second. Come on.

1251
01:56:16,289 --> 01:56:17,551
Keep digging.

1252
01:56:30,401 --> 01:56:33,131
- It had better be there, huh?
- Yes, yes.

1253
01:56:36,173 --> 01:56:37,764
Have you got it?

1254
01:56:39,209 --> 01:56:42,473
- Have you got it, huh?
- Yes, got it. Oh, yes.

1255
01:56:43,914 --> 01:56:45,176
Oh, yes.

1256
01:56:47,349 --> 01:56:48,942
Solomon.

1257
01:56:55,754 --> 01:56:58,724
Dia, what are you doing?

1258
01:56:59,225 --> 01:57:00,715
Dia.

1259
01:57:03,063 --> 01:57:04,961
What are you doing?

1260
01:57:09,834 --> 01:57:11,132
Of the proud Mende tribe.

1261
01:57:17,075 --> 01:57:21,943
You are a good boy
who loves soccer and school.

1262
01:57:24,246 --> 01:57:27,376
Your mother loves you so much.

1263
01:57:29,820 --> 01:57:32,617
She waits by the fire making plantains...

1264
01:57:32,788 --> 01:57:35,450
...and red palm oil stew
with your sister N'Yanda...

1265
01:57:37,726 --> 01:57:39,990
...and the new baby.

1266
01:57:48,902 --> 01:57:51,166
The cows wait for you.

1267
01:57:51,338 --> 01:57:57,139
And Babu, the wild dog
who minds no one but you.

1268
01:57:59,713 --> 01:58:03,045
I know they made you do bad things...

1269
01:58:03,217 --> 01:58:05,683
...but you are not a bad boy.

1270
01:58:08,888 --> 01:58:11,287
I am your father...

1271
01:58:12,991 --> 01:58:15,286
...who loves you.

1272
01:58:16,559 --> 01:58:20,325
And you will come home with me
and be my son again.

1273
01:58:45,752 --> 01:58:48,118
Solomon, we've got to move, huh?

1274
01:58:48,288 --> 01:58:49,845
We've got to--

1275
01:58:53,025 --> 01:58:55,722
Go, go! Move!

1276
01:58:58,497 --> 01:59:00,054
Move. Move.

1277
01:59:00,231 --> 01:59:01,527
Move, move, move!

1278
01:59:01,698 --> 01:59:04,725
Move! Move! Move!

1279
01:59:06,337 --> 01:59:07,564
How far?

1280
01:59:07,739 --> 01:59:09,798
There's an airstrip
at the top of that gorge.

1281
01:59:09,974 --> 01:59:12,066
A plane will meet us, huh?

1282
01:59:12,476 --> 01:59:14,842
Hey, stop. Stop.

1283
01:59:17,113 --> 01:59:21,106
Give it to me.
Come on, give it to me, huh?

1284
01:59:28,624 --> 01:59:31,683
Keep moving. They'll be tracking us.

1285
01:59:37,997 --> 01:59:40,055
Nabil, where are you?

1286
01:59:41,133 --> 01:59:43,760
I'm nearly there.
Tell me what's happening.

1287
01:59:43,935 --> 01:59:47,394
We're about 10 K's out, huh?
We've got it, my friend.

1288
01:59:47,572 --> 01:59:49,472
<i>- Who is we?
- The fisherman and his son.</i>

1289
01:59:49,640 --> 01:59:51,233
<i>Lose them.</i>

1290
02:00:05,387 --> 02:00:07,481
It's at the top of that ridge there, huh?

1291
02:00:07,657 --> 02:00:08,954
You must stop and rest.

1292
02:00:09,125 --> 02:00:11,957
What? And give up the damn stone?

1293
02:00:12,128 --> 02:00:14,187
Keep moving. Come on.

1294
02:00:48,827 --> 02:00:51,159
Come. Come, come.

1295
02:01:38,269 --> 02:01:40,566
I can't. Stop.

1296
02:01:40,737 --> 02:01:42,798
- Okay.
- Stop.

1297
02:02:11,266 --> 02:02:12,358
Come on.

1298
02:02:12,966 --> 02:02:15,560
No! God, no. Stop.

1299
02:02:16,669 --> 02:02:20,002
Christ. No more. No more.

1300
02:03:03,945 --> 02:03:05,639
Take it, huh?

1301
02:03:08,049 --> 02:03:11,245
- Mr. Archer--
- Take it, take it.

1302
02:03:18,324 --> 02:03:20,088
I thought you would steal it from me.

1303
02:03:21,928 --> 02:03:25,556
Yeah, yeah, it occurred to me, huh?

1304
02:03:36,506 --> 02:03:38,132
Listen...

1305
02:03:41,109 --> 02:03:43,508
...this is Maddy's card, huh?

1306
02:03:43,678 --> 02:03:45,839
You call her when
you get to Conakry, all right?

1307
02:03:50,084 --> 02:03:52,052
And don't trust that pilot for a second.

1308
02:03:52,219 --> 02:03:55,279
You point this at his head
if he fucks around, all right?

1309
02:03:55,456 --> 02:03:56,922
I can carry you.

1310
02:04:09,835 --> 02:04:11,302
You take your boy home, huh?

1311
02:04:16,474 --> 02:04:19,135
You take him home, huh?

1312
02:04:23,681 --> 02:04:25,443
- Go! Go!
- Go. Come on.

1313
02:04:26,284 --> 02:04:27,376
Go on!

1314
02:04:33,122 --> 02:04:34,987
Come on. Come on.

1315
02:04:41,798 --> 02:04:44,162
Archer, you're a dead man!

1316
02:04:44,332 --> 02:04:46,164
Yeah, yeah.

1317
02:05:16,861 --> 02:05:18,225
Dia.

1318
02:05:39,447 --> 02:05:40,607
Hello. Maddy Bowen.

1319
02:05:40,849 --> 02:05:42,679
Yeah.

1320
02:05:43,017 --> 02:05:44,678
Thought I'd never call, huh?

1321
02:05:45,586 --> 02:05:49,646
And I'm so glad you did.
Excuse me.

1322
02:05:51,625 --> 02:05:52,784
When am I gonna see you?

1323
02:05:53,926 --> 02:05:59,661
Maddy, I want you to do me
one more favor, huh?

1324
02:06:00,366 --> 02:06:04,893
I want you to go meet Solomon
in Conakry.

1325
02:06:05,104 --> 02:06:07,799
In Guinea?
Why do you want me to go to Guinea?

1326
02:06:10,807 --> 02:06:12,866
We found his son...

1327
02:06:13,843 --> 02:06:17,244
...but he's gonna need some help,
you understand?

1328
02:06:18,013 --> 02:06:19,106
<i>Maddy?</i>

1329
02:06:21,917 --> 02:06:23,782
You're hurt.

1330
02:06:24,418 --> 02:06:25,476
Are you hurt?

1331
02:06:25,653 --> 02:06:28,817
Yeah, well, I've got
a little problem here.

1332
02:06:33,394 --> 02:06:37,091
Okay. You--
You tell me where you are.

1333
02:06:40,365 --> 02:06:41,389
<i>Archer?</i>

1334
02:06:53,544 --> 02:06:58,278
I'm looking at an incredible view
right now.

1335
02:06:59,685 --> 02:07:01,312
I wish you were here, Maddy.

1336
02:07:01,487 --> 02:07:05,149
Okay, then I'm coming to be with you.
You just tell me where you are.

1337
02:07:08,358 --> 02:07:09,689
I don't think so.

1338
02:07:09,860 --> 02:07:13,191
Are you still in Kono? Because I can
get someone there to help you.

1339
02:07:13,362 --> 02:07:17,628
Maddy, you find someplace safe
for the boy, all right?

1340
02:07:17,800 --> 02:07:20,201
<i>And keep him out of sight.</i>

1341
02:07:20,803 --> 02:07:23,533
<i>And get Solomon to London.</i>

1342
02:07:26,674 --> 02:07:29,439
He's bringing something with him.

1343
02:07:30,109 --> 02:07:32,043
But he's gonna need your help.

1344
02:07:33,279 --> 02:07:35,109
Why aren't you bringing it yourself?

1345
02:07:36,616 --> 02:07:41,677
I'm saying it's a real story now.

1346
02:07:42,587 --> 02:07:44,315
And you can write the hell out of it.

1347
02:07:51,529 --> 02:07:54,053
I'm really happy I met you.

1348
02:07:55,633 --> 02:07:56,621
You know that?

1349
02:07:59,969 --> 02:08:02,097
Yeah, I'm...

1350
02:08:03,306 --> 02:08:06,365
I'm really happy I met you too.

1351
02:08:06,975 --> 02:08:10,968
<i>And I wish I could be there with you.</i>

1352
02:08:11,847 --> 02:08:13,814
That's all right.

1353
02:08:16,350 --> 02:08:18,751
I'm exactly where I'm supposed to be.

1354
02:09:12,366 --> 02:09:14,698
When we get to the stairs,
you just keep walking...

1355
02:09:14,868 --> 02:09:16,892
...and I'll wait for you here.

1356
02:09:17,470 --> 02:09:18,993
You're not coming.

1357
02:09:19,171 --> 02:09:22,437
I'm not here. Good luck.

1358
02:09:44,094 --> 02:09:46,756
You must understand, Mr. Vandy...

1359
02:09:46,930 --> 02:09:52,994
...that your diamond could have ended up
nowhere else but with us.

1360
02:09:56,307 --> 02:09:59,273
- It is not enough.
- I assure you, 2 million pounds...

1361
02:09:59,442 --> 02:10:03,307
...is more than anyone else will offer you
for that stone under the circumstances.

1362
02:10:03,477 --> 02:10:06,176
I want what was promised to me
by Mr. Archer.

1363
02:10:09,648 --> 02:10:12,174
- What was promised to you?
- My family.

1364
02:10:12,520 --> 02:10:14,509
When they are here,
you will get the stone.

1365
02:10:15,188 --> 02:10:16,814
I will have the money too.

1366
02:10:18,123 --> 02:10:19,647
Well, may I see what I'm buying?

1367
02:10:19,822 --> 02:10:22,587
You will get the stone
once my family is here.

1368
02:10:23,362 --> 02:10:25,158
How do I even know you've got it?

1369
02:12:33,043 --> 02:12:35,808
Can you comment on the diamonds
mined in Sierra Leone?

1370
02:12:35,977 --> 02:12:39,881
I'm not going to comment
on some sensationalist magazine article.

1371
02:12:40,047 --> 02:12:42,641
- What about Liberia?
- No comment. No comment.

1372
02:12:42,816 --> 02:12:45,216
- Mr. Van De Kaap--
- That's all I have to say.

1373
02:12:45,386 --> 02:12:46,787
The natural resources
of a country...

1374
02:12:48,789 --> 02:12:51,759
...are the property of its people.
They are not ours to steal...

1375
02:12:53,093 --> 02:12:58,552
<i>...or exploit in the name of our comfort,
our corporations, or our consumerism.</i>

1376
02:13:08,472 --> 02:13:10,532
They're ready for you, sir.

1377
02:13:12,042 --> 02:13:14,441
The Third World is not a world apart.

1378
02:13:14,611 --> 02:13:19,277
And the witness you will hear today
speaks on its behalf.

1379
02:13:19,447 --> 02:13:23,316
Let us hear the voice of that world.
Let us learn from that voice.

1380
02:13:23,485 --> 02:13:27,010
And let us ignore it no more.

1381
02:13:27,190 --> 02:13:30,520
Ladies and gentlemen,
Mr. Solomon Vandy.

